HEADWORD: Pikestaff
<hw>Pike"staff`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
staff, or shaft, of a pike.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A staff with a spike in the lower end, to guard
against slipping.</def> <rj><au>Sir W. Scott.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Piketail</ent>⟦br⟧
